-Friend. Friend, what's happening?
-I said, get out.

479
00:20:43,846 --> 00:20:44,973
-Okay.
-[doors slamming]

480
00:20:45,056 --> 00:20:46,599
-[Ivan] Buddy.
-[Andrei] What's going on?

481
00:20:46,683 --> 00:20:50,853
Can-- Can you-- Hey. Help us out here.
What's… What's happening here, huh?

482
00:20:51,521 --> 00:20:52,814
[loud clanking]

483
00:20:53,690 --> 00:20:54,607
Dig.

484
00:20:55,608 --> 00:20:56,693
[insects chirping]

485
00:21:00,071 --> 00:21:01,281
[in Brazilian Portuguese] Now.

486
00:21:03,074 --> 00:21:04,909
[upbeat music playing]

487
00:21:06,661 --> 00:21:08,371
[seagulls calling]

488
00:21:13,293 --> 00:21:15,461
Are you ever going to ask me
why we're here?

489
00:21:16,296 --> 00:21:17,297
[Morgan] Nope.

490
00:21:19,966 --> 00:21:21,843
Tareq was in trouble,

491
00:21:23,094 --> 00:21:26,681
and I offered to come here
in exchange for Ivan and Andrei's help.

492
00:21:29,017 --> 00:21:29,851
Wait, so…

493
00:21:31,853 --> 00:21:34,188
we're stuck out here
with the Brazilian cartel

494
00:21:34,272 --> 00:21:35,982
to help your boyfriend?

495
00:21:37,066 --> 00:21:37,900
Yeah.

496
00:21:38,401 --> 00:21:41,321
I mean, I didn't know it was
the cartel at the time, but yeah.

497
00:21:41,404 --> 00:21:42,530
[Morgan sighs]

498
00:21:42,613 --> 00:21:46,242
And I'm really, really sorry
for getting you involved in this.

499
00:21:46,326 --> 00:21:48,995
[music continues]

500
00:21:51,497 --> 00:21:52,707
[Morgan sighs]

501
00:21:53,958 --> 00:21:54,792
I'm sorry.

502
00:22:02,342 --> 00:22:03,843
I have to end things with Max.

503
00:22:03,926 --> 00:22:05,636
-What?
-[exhales loudly]

504
00:22:05,720 --> 00:22:10,099
I would never do something like that
for him. We've been together 17 years.

505
00:22:11,184 --> 00:22:16,981
[exhales] It's like, I've convinced myself
that there's some, uh, agenda

506
00:22:17,065 --> 00:22:19,650
to your, like… goodness.

507
00:22:19,734 --> 00:22:21,819
Like, it's not genuine or something,
because if it was,

508
00:22:21,903 --> 00:22:23,863
then I would only feel like
a bigger piece of shit,

509
00:22:23,946 --> 00:22:25,531
but there's not.

510
00:22:25,615 --> 00:22:27,450
You're just… you're somehow just

511
00:22:28,493 --> 00:22:29,494
a good person.

512
00:22:30,995 --> 00:22:33,206
It's so annoying.

513
00:22:33,289 --> 00:22:34,123
-Good person?
-Yeah.

514
00:22:34,207 --> 00:22:37,168
Have you been listening to me speak?
I put us both in so much danger.

515
00:22:37,251 --> 00:22:40,713
Whatever, dude. I wanted it.
You know it, I know it.

516
00:22:40,797 --> 00:22:42,340
-Okay.
-Oh.

517
00:22:43,883 --> 00:22:44,801
Fuck.

518
00:22:45,718 --> 00:22:48,513
I think you're just coming off
of a lot of cocaine.

519
00:22:48,596 --> 00:22:51,057
That wasn't a lot of cocaine.
I've done way more than that.

520
00:22:51,140 --> 00:22:53,017
-Excuse me?
-Yeah, that wasn't even a lot.

521
00:22:53,101 --> 00:22:54,894
Morgan, come on. That's scary.

522
00:22:54,977 --> 00:22:55,812
Hey!

523
00:22:58,981 --> 00:23:00,900
-[Nicky] Is he talking to me?
-I…

524
00:23:00,983 --> 00:23:03,444
-Are you talking to me?
-Yes, you. Come.

525
00:23:03,528 --> 00:23:05,530
What the fuck does he want from me?

526
00:23:06,364 --> 00:23:08,533
[tense music playing]

527
00:23:17,208 --> 00:23:18,751
[music ends]

528
00:23:19,335 --> 00:23:20,169
[Andrei grunts]

529
00:23:20,253 --> 00:23:21,170
[Ivan] Sir.

530
00:23:21,671 --> 00:23:23,214
Sir. Look.

531
00:23:23,881 --> 00:23:26,426
We can handle 100 cows a month.

532
00:23:26,509 --> 00:23:28,803
One hundred-- Possibly more.

533
00:23:28,886 --> 00:23:32,306
And we are slowly
inching into their territory,

534
00:23:32,390 --> 00:23:34,058
so the Italians won't see it coming.

535
00:23:34,142 --> 00:23:38,563
Do you want to tell us why the minister
and schoolteacher are actually here?

536
00:23:39,147 --> 00:23:42,150
What? What… what… what do you mean?
We went through this last night.

537
00:23:42,233 --> 00:23:43,943
-I mean--
-I'm asking for the truth.

538
00:23:44,527 --> 00:23:47,280
It has nothing to do
with the Turk going missing?

539
00:23:47,363 --> 00:23:48,406
[insects chirping]

540
00:23:48,489 --> 00:23:49,824
No. Who told you that? No.

541
00:23:49,907 --> 00:23:51,576
[in Brazilian Portuguese] For fuck's sake.

542
00:23:51,659 --> 00:23:53,786
[in English] Do not fuck with me.

543
00:23:53,870 --> 00:23:57,415
If there is a loose end out there,
we need to know about it.

544
00:23:57,498 --> 00:24:01,210
The-- there's nothing to worry about.
Trust me.

545
00:24:02,003 --> 00:24:02,837
[gun cocks]

546
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:04,255
-[Andrei shouts]
-[shovel clanking]

547
00:24:04,338 --> 00:24:05,590
I took care of him!

548
00:24:07,175 --> 00:24:08,092
[spits]

549
00:24:08,676 --> 00:24:10,678
Yusuf ran away to Turkey.

550
00:24:10,761 --> 00:24:14,265
But I had someone over there
take care of it because… [exhales sharply]

551
00:24:16,350 --> 00:24:18,394
[panting] If there is a problem,

552
00:24:18,478 --> 00:24:19,729
we fix it.

553
00:24:19,812 --> 00:24:23,274
And I will do it again if anything else
gets in the way of our business.

554
00:24:23,357 --> 00:24:24,901
[panting]

555
00:24:24,984 --> 00:24:27,445
So, do we have a deal?

556
00:24:28,279 --> 00:24:30,281
Or do we keep digging? [inhales deeply]

557
00:24:31,699 --> 00:24:33,284
[Andrei breathing heavily]

558
00:24:34,410 --> 00:24:35,536
[upbeat music playing]

559
00:24:35,620 --> 00:24:37,246
[in Brazilian Portuguese] Leave us alone.

560
00:24:41,959 --> 00:24:43,794
[Paolo speaking Brazilian Portuguese]

561
00:24:44,795 --> 00:24:46,923
-[lock clicks]
-Do we need to lock the door? Okay.

562
00:24:47,006 --> 00:24:48,716
-[Paolo] Soundproof.
-Yeah.

563
00:24:48,799 --> 00:24:50,301
-Incredible, right?
-Mm.

564
00:24:50,384 --> 00:24:52,303
It does look thin,
but you can't hear a thing.

565
00:24:52,386 --> 00:24:53,930
-[Nicky chuckles nervously]
-Mm.

566
00:24:54,013 --> 00:24:56,390
Yeah. It's a beautiful boat.

567
00:24:56,474 --> 00:24:57,892
Did you… [inhales deeply]

568
00:24:57,975 --> 00:25:00,353
…sail it here from Brazil or…?

569
00:25:00,436 --> 00:25:02,313
Well, that would be fucking stupid.

570
00:25:02,396 --> 00:25:03,773
No. Mexico.

571
00:25:03,856 --> 00:25:04,732
I'm Mexican.

572
00:25:04,815 --> 00:25:08,027
Oh, I'm… I'm sorry.
I thought you were… from Brazil.

573
00:25:08,110 --> 00:25:10,321
No, no, no. I'm from Sinaloa.

574
00:25:10,404 --> 00:25:12,698
I killed my way to Brazil.

575
00:25:12,782 --> 00:25:14,200
-Just kidding.
-[chuckles nervously]

576
00:25:14,283 --> 00:25:17,203
I just go where the powder blows,
as they say.

577
00:25:20,081 --> 00:25:20,915
Sit.

578
00:25:21,999 --> 00:25:22,875
Come here.

579
00:25:25,503 --> 00:25:26,879
What do you want to drink?

580
00:25:26,963 --> 00:25:29,173
I have a splitting headache,
so just water, please.

581
00:25:29,257 --> 00:25:32,885
I don't like drinking alone.
There's a judgment to it. Tequila?

582
00:25:34,178 --> 00:25:36,013
-Uh… Yep.
-[cork popping]

583
00:25:37,723 --> 00:25:40,017
-You had fun last night?
-Mm.

584
00:25:40,768 --> 00:25:43,938
Dinner plates aren't usually empty.
Sorry about that.

585
00:25:44,021 --> 00:25:46,732
I had to make sure that you were serious.

586
00:25:47,233 --> 00:25:48,192
Oh…

587
00:25:49,193 --> 00:25:50,736
But it was good shit, huh?

588
00:25:50,820 --> 00:25:52,572
Yeah, it was, uh… [sniffs]

589
00:25:53,531 --> 00:25:56,409
Uh… really good shit. Very pure.

590
00:25:57,118 --> 00:25:58,703
-Very nice.
-[Paolo inhales]

591
00:25:59,829 --> 00:26:00,705
So,

592
00:26:01,330 --> 00:26:03,124
I heard that you met my son.

593
00:26:05,001 --> 00:26:06,919
I don't know who your son…

594
00:26:07,003 --> 00:26:08,754
-Filipe.
-Oh.

595
00:26:08,838 --> 00:26:11,591
Yeah, he has a good head of hair?

596
00:26:11,674 --> 00:26:13,092
I think we might have… [inhales]

597
00:26:13,175 --> 00:26:14,927
…crossed paths at the club.

598
00:26:15,011 --> 00:26:16,762
We're very different, he and I.

599
00:26:17,805 --> 00:26:18,848
[Nicky] Okay.

600
00:26:18,931 --> 00:26:20,016
He's a homosexual.

601
00:26:20,099 --> 00:26:21,559
Interesting. [inhales]

602
00:26:23,144 --> 00:26:25,855
-Does he know that you know that…
-No.

603
00:26:26,981 --> 00:26:27,857
Hmm.

604
00:26:28,608 --> 00:26:32,236
It might be nice to… to let him know
that you know and that you're fi--

605
00:26:32,320 --> 00:26:33,654
I won't be doing that.

606
00:26:34,530 --> 00:26:38,200
Hm. I mean, as… as somebody
who has hidden parts of myself away,

607
00:26:38,284 --> 00:26:39,785
I can tell you that, you know,

608
00:26:39,869 --> 00:26:42,788
knowing that your family is on your side,
it… it means the world.

609
00:26:42,872 --> 00:26:44,624
I killed my father with a butter knife.

610
00:26:44,707 --> 00:26:46,542
[phone ringing]

611
00:26:46,626 --> 00:26:47,710
[tense music playing]

612
00:26:47,793 --> 00:26:49,211
[in Brazilian Portuguese] Heitor.

613
00:26:50,129 --> 00:26:51,005
Speak.

614
00:26:52,298 --> 00:26:53,424
You believe him?

615
00:26:54,175 --> 00:26:55,259
Okay then.

616
00:26:55,926 --> 00:26:56,802
Bye-bye.

617
00:26:57,303 --> 00:26:58,220
[in English] Well,

618
00:26:58,804 --> 00:27:00,765
looks like I'm not going
to have to kill you today.

619
00:27:00,848 --> 00:27:01,766
[music ends]

620
00:27:03,476 --> 00:27:05,019
We have a deal to make.

621
00:27:06,187 --> 00:27:07,480
[clears throat, sniffs]

622
00:27:08,856 --> 00:27:09,774
Okay.

623
00:27:10,274 --> 00:27:11,442
-Yeah.
-[glasses clinking]

624
00:27:13,527 --> 00:27:15,404
[tense music resumes]

625
00:27:15,488 --> 00:27:16,906
[Paolo breathing loudly]

626
00:27:17,865 --> 00:27:19,825
[gagging, gulping]

627
00:27:21,202 --> 00:27:22,620
[glass clinking]

628
00:27:22,703 --> 00:27:24,163
[Paolo] Good evening, everyone.

629
00:27:24,664 --> 00:27:27,124
To think that there was a very real chance

630
00:27:27,208 --> 00:27:31,629
that this entire team of Americans
and Russians would be shot dead.

631
00:27:31,712 --> 00:27:34,340
-[men laughing]
-[Paolo] But, look at us now.

632
00:27:34,423 --> 00:27:35,675
[laughs] Cheers!

633
00:27:35,758 --> 00:27:38,678
-[Paolo toasting in Brazilian Portuguese]
-[men toasting, cheering]

634
00:27:38,761 --> 00:27:40,846
-[Ivan speaking indistinctly]
-[glasses clinking]

635
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:42,848
-Is he joking?
-I don't know.

636
00:27:42,932 --> 00:27:44,725
[Morgan breathes heavily]

637
00:27:44,809 --> 00:27:46,268
[upbeat music playing]

638
00:27:46,352 --> 00:27:50,731
Hey, is there any part of you
that likes this, like, what we're doing?

639
00:27:51,315 --> 00:27:55,319
Absolutely not. I literally
cannot wait to get out of this.

640
00:27:55,986 --> 00:27:57,321
[Morgan sighs deeply]

641
00:27:57,405 --> 00:28:00,282
I think there's something wrong
with me. [smacks lips]

642
00:28:00,866 --> 00:28:02,993
Morgan, there's nothing wrong
with you, okay?

643
00:28:03,077 --> 00:28:07,707
You might be restless and easily bored
and stuck in a bad relationship

644
00:28:07,790 --> 00:28:11,919
and, you know, likely undiagnosed ADHD.

645
00:28:12,002 --> 00:28:14,255
And you should absolutely invest
in a day planner,

646
00:28:14,338 --> 00:28:16,841
but there is nothing wrong with you. Okay?

647
00:28:16,924 --> 00:28:18,300
[music continues]

648
00:28:19,260 --> 00:28:20,720
[Morgan] Yeah. Wow.

649
00:28:21,595 --> 00:28:23,180
Thank you for saying that.

650
00:28:25,474 --> 00:28:27,935
Yeah, I think I really needed to, um,

651
00:28:28,769 --> 00:28:29,687
hear that.

652
00:28:29,770 --> 00:28:31,480
-[inhales]
-Did you do more cocaine?

653
00:28:31,564 --> 00:28:33,274
No. Like one bump, two bumps.

654
00:28:33,357 --> 00:28:35,526
One bump. Are you using?

655
00:28:35,609 --> 00:28:37,069
-"Using"?
-[Nicky] Like, I don't know.

656
00:28:37,153 --> 00:28:39,280
-Is it 1997? "I'm using"?
-[Nicky] It's like a weird…

657
00:28:39,363 --> 00:28:41,532
I'm just saying.
What, suddenly you're a cokehead?

658
00:28:41,615 --> 00:28:43,492
You're acting like it's, like--
Like it's meth.

659
00:28:43,576 --> 00:28:45,244
You're saying it like it's meth.

660
00:28:45,327 --> 00:28:47,163
-[exhales loudly]
-Well, it's something.

661
00:28:48,748 --> 00:28:50,374
-That's nice.
-[music gets louder]

662
00:28:50,458 --> 00:28:51,375
I just have to say,

663
00:28:51,959 --> 00:28:55,629
I think that this trip has been
a lifeline for us, don't you think?

664
00:28:56,964 --> 00:28:58,632
[raised voice] It's been something.

665
00:28:58,716 --> 00:29:00,551
-Something nice, right?
-Yup.

666
00:29:00,634 --> 00:29:02,428
I know this sounds corny.

667
00:29:03,763 --> 00:29:06,974
But I've really enjoyed my time with you.

668
00:29:07,057 --> 00:29:08,809
[music continues loudly]

669
00:29:09,435 --> 00:29:10,436
[muffled gunshot]

670
00:29:10,519 --> 00:29:12,188
-[screaming]
-[muffled gunshots]

671
00:29:12,271 --> 00:29:13,606
[screaming]

672
00:29:14,899 --> 00:29:16,942
-[loud gunshot]
-[Nicky screaming]

673
00:29:18,444 --> 00:29:21,197
-[screaming]
-[glass breaking]

674
00:29:23,616 --> 00:29:24,533
[Nicky heaving]

675
00:29:25,576 --> 00:29:27,578
-[Nicky cries out]
-[Morgan gasps]

676
00:29:28,245 --> 00:29:29,789
-[door closes]
-[Morgan gasps]

677
00:29:30,623 --> 00:29:32,249
-[door closes]
-[gasping]

678
00:29:34,168 --> 00:29:35,836
Holy… Holy fuck.

679
00:29:37,004 --> 00:29:37,963
[gasping]

680
00:29:38,547 --> 00:29:39,465
[strangled cry]

681
00:29:40,299 --> 00:29:41,383
[gasping]

682
00:29:43,219 --> 00:29:44,220
[strangled cry]

683
00:29:44,929 --> 00:29:46,013
[gasping]

684
00:29:48,891 --> 00:29:49,934
[exhales loudly]

685
00:29:50,434 --> 00:29:51,352
Fuck.

686
00:29:53,437 --> 00:29:55,356
[dark percussive music playing]

687
00:31:16,687 --> 00:31:18,439
[music ends]
